Description:
    Generate a Tahi plugin.

Example:
    rails generate tahi:plugin PLUGIN_NAME

    If PATH is not specified, engines/PLUGIN_NAME will be used.

    This will create:
        engines/PLUGIN_NAME/README.rdoc
        engines/PLUGIN_NAME/Rakefile
        engines/PLUGIN_NAME/PLUGIN_NAME.gemspec
        engines/PLUGIN_NAME/MIT-LICENSE
        engines/PLUGIN_NAME/.gitignore
        engines/PLUGIN_NAME/Gemfile
        engines/PLUGIN_NAME/app
        engines/PLUGIN_NAME/app/controllers/PLUGIN_NAME/application_controller.rb
        engines/PLUGIN_NAME/app/helpers/PLUGIN_NAME/application_helper.rb
        engines/PLUGIN_NAME/app/mailers
        engines/PLUGIN_NAME/app/models
        engines/PLUGIN_NAME/app/views/layouts/PLUGIN_NAME/application.html.erb
        engines/PLUGIN_NAME/app/assets/images/PLUGIN_NAME
        engines/PLUGIN_NAME/app/assets/images/PLUGIN_NAME/.keep
        engines/PLUGIN_NAME/config/routes.rb
        engines/PLUGIN_NAME/lib/PLUGIN_NAME.rb
        engines/PLUGIN_NAME/lib/tasks/PLUGIN_NAME_tasks.rake
        engines/PLUGIN_NAME/lib/PLUGIN_NAME/version.rb
        engines/PLUGIN_NAME/lib/PLUGIN_NAME/engine.rb
        engines/PLUGIN_NAME/app/assets/javascripts/PLUGIN_NAME/application.js
        engines/PLUGIN_NAME/bin
        engines/PLUGIN_NAME/bin/rails
        engines/PLUGIN_NAME/client/index.js
        engines/PLUGIN_NAME/client/package.json
        engines/PLUGIN_NAME/client/styles/PLUGIN_NAME/application.scss
